There is no evidence supporting a widespread or progressive increase in vancomycin minimum inhibitory concentrations (MICs) globally; instead, resistance arises through discrete genetic mutations like VanA/VanB leading to fully resistant strains. This indicates that concerns about 'mic creep' are based more on misinterpretation of high-MIC cases versus actual measurable decline in drug efficacy due to specific resistances.

